New Records: Ayoub El Kaabi scored a hat-trick and contributed an assist in Morocco's 6-0 victory over Congo.
Morocco achieved a 6-0 scoreline in their World Cup qualifier against Congo, the highest score in the match.
Key Match Events: Morocco opened the scoring in the 8th minute with a goal by Azzedine Ounahi.
Ayoub El Kaabi scored his first goal in the 16th minute to make it 2-0 for Morocco.
El Kaabi completed his hat-trick with a header in the 53rd minute.
Congo was reduced to three yellow cards due to persistent fouls.
Pre-Game Insights: Morocco dominated from the start, with high pressure and early goals.
The match was a crucial step for Morocco in their World Cup qualification journey.
Post-Match Reflections: Ayoub El Kaabi was praised for his outstanding performance with three goals and an assist.
Morocco's victory showcased their attacking strength and dominance over Congo.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Congo's defense struggled throughout the match, unable to contain Morocco's forwards.
Morocco's solid defense and clinical finishing were key factors in the match.
